presenting as her husband.

00:36:36.216 --> 00:36:38.340
And I don't know whether
he was her husband or not.

00:36:38.340 --> 00:36:40.620
And she came as
an emergency case,

00:36:40.620 --> 00:36:43.560
as a case of ruptured
ectopic pregnancy.

00:36:43.560 --> 00:36:46.410
And at that time, it was
not a highlighted case.

00:36:46.410 --> 00:36:48.750
She came to us as
a simple patient.

00:36:48.750 --> 00:36:51.360
And for that,
emergency laparotomy

00:36:51.360 --> 00:36:53.720
has to be done to save her life.

00:36:53.720 --> 00:36:57.740
But in her statement, she
names Shanu not Kaleem.

00:36:57.740 --> 00:36:59.920
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:37:27.210 --> 00:37:29.070
Sima Mischa works
with a group that

00:37:29.070 --> 00:37:31.710
has had couples who
faced risks for having

00:37:31.710 --> 00:37:33.960
broken family taboos.

00:37:33.960 --> 00:37:37.600
To her, the Meerat incident
follows a familiar pattern.

00:37:37.600 --> 00:37:42.960
What I find is very common
is adult men and women get

00:37:42.960 --> 00:37:47.280
into relationships and when
the families don't like it,

00:37:47.280 --> 00:37:49.090
then all hell breaks loose.

00:37:49.090 --> 00:37:51.390
And they go off and file a
whole lot of criminal cases

00:37:51.390 --> 00:37:52.920
against the boy.

00:37:52.920 --> 00:37:54.700
And the police then forces them.

00:37:54.700 --> 00:37:56.610
It's a typical
pattern that we've

00:37:56.610 --> 00:37:59.079
been working in the Uttar
Pradesh for the last 10 years

00:37:59.079 --> 00:38:00.120
I've seen this happening.

00:38:00.120 --> 00:38:03.720
And there's so much pressure on
the girl to take the girl back.

00:38:03.720 --> 00:38:04.830
Let me say this.

00:38:04.830 --> 00:38:07.590
This is not about
discrediting the testimony

00:38:07.590 --> 00:38:09.030
of a rape survivor.

00:38:09.030 --> 00:38:11.910
We know how difficult it
is for women to speak up

00:38:11.910 --> 00:38:13.350
about sexual violence.

00:38:13.350 --> 00:38:15.600
But here's the problem
with the Meerat case.

00:38:15.600 --> 00:38:18.960
That the [INAUDIBLE] has
already pronounced its verdict

00:38:18.960 --> 00:38:21.960
without factoring in any
of these inconsistencies.

00:38:21.960 --> 00:38:25.110
Even while the investigation
is at a nascent stage.

00:38:25.110 --> 00:38:28.140
Now this places the
individuals at the heart of it

00:38:28.140 --> 00:38:29.320
at great risk.

00:38:29.320 --> 00:38:32.435
But also has incendiary
social repercussions.

00:38:32.435 --> 00:38:37.720
And hence the need to look
closely at the Meerat episode.

00:38:37.720 --> 00:38:41.080
Right, let's just pull
up that last image.

00:38:41.080 --> 00:38:44.800
So this was an instance
where actually there

00:38:44.800 --> 00:38:47.200
was a happy ending.

00:38:47.200 --> 00:38:50.050
This is the young woman
that we just interviewed.

00:38:50.050 --> 00:38:53.590
So she finally came out in the
open, along with her partner

00:38:53.590 --> 00:38:55.660
Kaleem, the person
whose identity

00:38:55.660 --> 00:38:57.160
she was hiding throughout.

00:38:57.160 --> 00:39:00.280
And who she had actually
named as an accomplice.

00:39:00.280 --> 00:39:02.230
So they couldn't control--

00:39:02.230 --> 00:39:04.720
they couldn't contain
the emotions anymore.

00:39:04.720 --> 00:39:07.116
And they broke against
the family taboo.

00:39:07.116 --> 00:39:08.740
They broke against
the kind of pressure

00:39:08.740 --> 00:39:12.040
that was being placed by
the political forces that

00:39:12.040 --> 00:39:13.090
had got involved.

00:39:13.090 --> 00:39:14.430
And they got married.

00:39:14.430 --> 00:39:17.980
And for a while, they
lived in police custody--

00:39:17.980 --> 00:39:20.380
not in police custody, but
under police protection.

00:39:20.380 --> 00:39:23.070
But finally, now, they're
able to come out of that

00:39:23.070 --> 00:39:25.050
and they are united.

00:39:25.050 --> 00:39:27.400
But it just gives
you one more example

00:39:27.400 --> 00:39:32.140
of how just ordinary
interfaith relationships get

00:39:32.140 --> 00:39:34.180
criminalized and politicized.

00:39:34.180 --> 00:39:38.750
And that really is the
story of how this Love Jihad

00:39:38.750 --> 00:39:40.720
myth has been built up.

00:39:40.720 --> 00:39:43.060
So in conclusion, I'll
say there are more video.

00:39:43.060 --> 00:39:44.620
But we're running short of time.

00:39:44.620 --> 00:39:49.420
So I'll wrap up and then we
can take more of these aspects

00:39:49.420 --> 00:39:50.610
into the discussion.

00:39:50.610 --> 00:39:54.130
That it could be argued that
the slow poisoning of the well,

00:39:54.130 --> 00:40:00.100
or the air, is as if not more
toxic than egregious shocks

00:40:00.100 --> 00:40:03.070
and the egregious crimes
on Indian democracy

00:40:03.070 --> 00:40:04.570
by past political regimes.

00:40:04.570 --> 00:40:05.734
Thank you very much.

00:40:05.734 --> 00:40:09.052
