00:54:21.340 --> 00:54:26.100
just a euphemism for a wave
of unreason and humanity

00:54:26.100 --> 00:54:28.710
that was sweeping the country.

00:54:28.710 --> 00:54:33.900
On that occasion, I decided to
consult my young friend Rohit

00:54:33.900 --> 00:54:38.940
De and spoke mostly about
constitutional morality.

00:54:38.940 --> 00:54:41.190
The way in which
Ambedkar had spoken

00:54:41.190 --> 00:54:45.930
about it and other members
of the constituent assembly.

00:54:45.930 --> 00:54:48.600
But even in that
speech towards the end,

00:54:48.600 --> 00:54:51.330
I again had to mourn a death.

00:54:51.330 --> 00:54:55.260
And I said I had mourned
the death of Mohsin Shaikh,

00:54:55.260 --> 00:54:57.480
the computer engineer in Pune.

00:54:57.480 --> 00:55:00.450
This happened days after the
new government took power.

00:55:00.450 --> 00:55:03.660
Today I mourn the death of
Muhammad Akhlaq and others

00:55:03.660 --> 00:55:06.660
who have been victims in
recent months of the poison

00:55:06.660 --> 00:55:09.390
of religious hatred.

00:55:09.390 --> 00:55:11.490
In the name of
bygone generations

00:55:11.490 --> 00:55:14.190
that have welded the Indian
people into a nation,

00:55:14.190 --> 00:55:17.640
I invoke the noble meaning
of the word Akhlaq.

00:55:17.640 --> 00:55:19.530
What does Akhlaq mean?

00:55:19.530 --> 00:55:21.120
It means ethics.

00:55:21.120 --> 00:55:24.300
And I urge those who hold the
reins of power in our country

00:55:24.300 --> 00:55:27.990
today, especially our Prime
Minister and our Home Minister,

00:55:27.990 --> 00:55:31.200
to uphold the fundamental right
to life and liberty of all

00:55:31.200 --> 00:55:34.300
our citizens and
abide by Akhlaq,

00:55:34.300 --> 00:55:37.500
the ethics of good governance
that have informed the very

00:55:37.500 --> 00:55:43.600
best of Indian political thought
and practice through the ages.

00:55:43.600 --> 00:55:48.760
Now in addition to the
kind of hate speech

00:55:48.760 --> 00:55:54.060
that you heard played by people
holding important offices,

00:55:54.060 --> 00:55:58.830
there is something else that
also needs to be underlined.

00:55:58.830 --> 00:56:06.300
And that is the feeblest of
disavowels or disapprovals

00:56:06.300 --> 00:56:11.250
coming from those occupying the
top most echelons of government

00:56:11.250 --> 00:56:16.890
when these kinds of horrendous
lynchings have taken place.

00:56:16.890 --> 00:56:21.600
And you know, Modi has
been typically very late

00:56:21.600 --> 00:56:24.390
and then he has not
been unambiguous

00:56:24.390 --> 00:56:25.900
in the condemnation.

00:56:25.900 --> 00:56:32.540
And so this is in some
ways a part of a strategy.

00:56:32.540 --> 00:56:37.830
It is in some ways more
insidious than bigger riots

00:56:37.830 --> 00:56:42.870
or even pogroms of the sort
that we saw in Gujarat in 2002.

00:56:42.870 --> 00:56:45.660
You simply have to
make a spectacle

00:56:45.660 --> 00:56:48.900
of killing one person or two.

00:56:48.900 --> 00:56:55.180
And doing so you can then
terrify an entire community.

00:56:55.180 --> 00:56:58.830
And this is what is being
done to the Muslims and Dalits

00:56:58.830 --> 00:57:00.190
in our country today.

00:57:00.190 --> 00:57:04.290
So it is very much a
part of the strategy that

00:57:04.290 --> 00:57:10.560
has been adopted by those
who basically confuse

00:57:10.560 --> 00:57:18.000
religious majoritarianism with
democracy and deliberately so.

00:57:18.000 --> 00:57:22.010
So I think I'll stop my
initial comments here,

00:57:22.010 --> 00:57:26.550
excepting that I did want to
say a few words about what

00:57:26.550 --> 00:57:31.050
has happened in terms of
another kind of institution

00:57:31.050 --> 00:57:33.530
that has been
under grave threat.

00:57:33.530 --> 00:57:37.020
And I can speak about it
in question and answer.

00:57:37.020 --> 00:57:41.010
And this is what has been done
to the institutions of higher

00:57:41.010 --> 00:57:43.540
education in our country.

00:57:43.540 --> 00:57:45.750
And once again, there
was a major debate

00:57:45.750 --> 00:57:51.510
in February of 2016 on
the current situation

00:57:51.510 --> 00:57:53.950
in universities in our country.

00:57:53.950 --> 00:57:56.340
This happened soon
after the suicide

00:57:56.340 --> 00:58:01.030
of Rohith Vemula of
Hyderabad Central University.

00:58:01.030 --> 00:58:03.330
And what has happened
in our country

00:58:03.330 --> 00:58:08.070
is that people from
marginalized backgrounds

00:58:08.070 --> 00:58:11.680
have been given access
to our universities,

00:58:11.680 --> 00:58:14.070
including our
central universities.

00:58:14.070 --> 00:58:20.340
But they have not really been
included as equal citizens.

00:58:20.340 --> 00:58:24.630
So there was neglect
before, but now there

00:58:24.630 --> 00:58:27.840
is direct onslaught
by the state forces.

00:58:27.840 --> 00:58:31.320
And soon after the
Hyderabad incident,

00:58:31.320 --> 00:58:33.480
and I spoke about
Rohith Vemula suicide

00:58:33.480 --> 00:58:36.780
in the course of
my speech, there

00:58:36.780 --> 00:58:39.980
was the crisis in
Jawaharlal Nehru University.

00:58:39.980 --> 00:58:42.580
And students, including the
President of the Jawaharlal

00:58:42.580 --> 00:58:48.270
Nehru Students Union,
was arrested and charged

00:58:48.270 --> 00:58:50.530
with sedition.

00:58:50.530 --> 00:58:54.570
And after the
arrested students were

00:58:54.570 --> 00:58:59.280
brought to the court premises
of Patiala House in New Delhi,

00:58:59.280 --> 00:59:02.580
the storm troopers, the
black coated storm troopers

00:59:02.580 --> 00:59:06.030
of the ruling party,
attacked teachers

00:59:06.030 --> 00:59:10.740
and students and journalists
within the premises

00:59:10.740 --> 00:59:13.200
of the judiciary.

00:59:13.200 --> 00:59:16.650
And there's been a
systematic attack on higher

00:59:16.650 --> 00:59:19.330
educational institutions.

00:59:19.330 --> 00:59:25.560
And there is almost
a deliberate policy

00:59:25.560 --> 00:59:32.760
to demoralize our best public
institutions of higher learning

00:59:32.760 --> 00:59:35.990
through the drafting of a new
higher education commission

00:59:35.990 --> 00:59:36.770
bill.

00:59:36.770 --> 00:59:38.930
Which is, of course,
being resisted.

00:59:38.930 --> 00:59:43.610
And also there has not been a
single major central or state

00:59:43.610 --> 00:59:45.680
university that
has been included

00:59:45.680 --> 00:59:49.640
on the list of institutions
of eminence chosen

00:59:49.640 --> 00:59:54.830
by a committee appointed by
Prime Minister Narendra Modi,

00:59:54.830 --> 01:00:00.230
even though a non-existent
university to be established

01:00:00.230 --> 01:00:03.500
by India's leading
industrialist has been

01:00:03.500 --> 01:00:05.430
given that particular label.

01:00:05.430 --> 01:00:08.930
So of course, the media
has been under attack

01:00:08.930 --> 01:00:10.670
and there have been
other institutions

01:00:10.670 --> 01:00:13.100
that have been under siege.

01:00:13.100 --> 01:00:16.520
But we, sitting at a
university, must also

01:00:16.520 --> 01:00:21.560
consider what is happening in
the domain of higher education

01:00:21.560 --> 01:00:26.870
in India in this atmosphere
of democratic authoritarianism

01:00:26.870 --> 01:00:30.140
using a strategy of
religious majoritarianism

01:00:30.140 --> 01:00:34.160
to win majorities in
India's Parliament.

01:00:34.160 --> 01:00:34.670
Thank you.

01:00:34.670 --> 01:00:36.080
Thank you very much, Sugata.

