The question of complicity
that both of you brought up

01:00:40.190 --> 01:00:42.050
is certainly a
thread that is moving

01:00:42.050 --> 01:00:46.440
through the various comments.

01:00:46.440 --> 01:00:51.000
In addition to the media
and governance and the law,

01:00:51.000 --> 01:00:55.250
which we had, I think the
issue of higher education

01:00:55.250 --> 01:00:59.030
now emerges as another
topic, another item

01:00:59.030 --> 01:01:00.180
for our discussion.

01:01:00.180 --> 01:01:02.910
But with it, I think
also the concern

01:01:02.910 --> 01:01:06.170
not only for higher education,
but for education more

01:01:06.170 --> 01:01:07.340
generally.

01:01:07.340 --> 01:01:10.620
The rewriting and the
tampering of school books,

01:01:10.620 --> 01:01:13.550
which we know about.

01:01:13.550 --> 01:01:19.460
And also the infestation
of these ideas of exclusion

01:01:19.460 --> 01:01:22.397
at the level of
school education.

01:01:22.397 --> 01:01:24.230
I think this is something
we should look at.

01:01:24.230 --> 01:01:28.160
But turning to you, Rohit in the
context of these conversations.

01:01:28.160 --> 01:01:31.290
Of course, very keen to
see what you have to say.

01:01:31.290 --> 01:01:34.280
But one issue that
was just brought up,

01:01:34.280 --> 01:01:36.950
which I think is
something that I would

01:01:36.950 --> 01:01:40.760
love to hear you speaking
about, is the use

01:01:40.760 --> 01:01:42.830
