people and not so young people.

01:50:39.820 --> 01:50:42.670
I think this tendency
to just forward things

01:50:42.670 --> 01:50:45.560
and just shoot things
off has to stop.

01:50:45.560 --> 01:50:47.410
i mean, you need to
control yourself.

01:50:47.410 --> 01:50:51.364
This is a civil
society out of control.

01:50:51.364 --> 01:50:54.210
That's what I think.

01:50:54.210 --> 01:50:57.060
Then I think I don't know
anything else to respond to.

01:50:57.060 --> 01:51:00.120
But you know, just to
support, in this very room,

01:51:00.120 --> 01:51:03.000
in this very room
we once had a very

01:51:03.000 --> 01:51:07.080
fine presidential
historian who had written

01:51:07.080 --> 01:51:09.360
a blog which had gone viral.

01:51:09.360 --> 01:51:13.500
And my colleague,
Steve, said to me,

01:51:13.500 --> 01:51:15.060
you know maybe we
should have her.

01:51:15.060 --> 01:51:17.340
So we had her on a very
distinguished panel.

01:51:17.340 --> 01:51:19.890
And well, the story she told
us so much, [INAUDIBLE]..

01:51:19.890 --> 01:51:23.970
She said I was writing a
rather dull academic article

01:51:23.970 --> 01:51:28.110
and then some thought came
to me and I wrote a blog.

01:51:28.110 --> 01:51:31.140
I posted it and I
went out to dinner.

01:51:31.140 --> 01:51:34.890
And I came back to find
that 2,000 people or 300

01:51:34.890 --> 01:51:36.910
people or 600 people
had responded to it.

01:51:36.910 --> 01:51:41.580
She said in retrospect, I
don't think it was very good.

01:51:41.580 --> 01:51:45.510
But once the
virality carries on,

01:51:45.510 --> 01:51:47.580
then opinion gets to be formed.

01:51:47.580 --> 01:51:50.310
We've got to be very careful
about public opinion.

01:51:50.310 --> 01:51:51.870
Well, you form public opinion.

01:51:51.870 --> 01:51:53.790
But don't send things
that are dubious.

01:51:53.790 --> 01:51:55.740
I do think a lot
of people do that.

01:51:55.740 --> 01:51:56.860
People will do that.

